    "description": "This ~~WIP~~ PR is the product of my experiment with using flake8 to lint the codebase today.  I've started with the analysis_modules section of the code. For now, I'm going to focus only on errors that can lead to functional bugs: missing imports, unused imports, unused assignments, and undefined variables.\r\n\r\nTo accomplish this, I've added a number of flake8 configuration settings to the top-level setup.cfg file in the repository. These rules were chosen to be ignored if they only affect code style and do not have any functional implications.  I'm using an explicit list of rules to ignore to simplify the process of  one day removing sme or all these rules, just in case we want to do so eventually.\r\n\r\nI'm issuing this now to get feedback about the changes I've made - have I done anything objectionable? I'd also like to see if any of these changes broke any of the analysis modules, to gauge the riskiness of the rules I've decided to implement. This is hopefully a big enough section of the codebase to get a good estimate of the risk of introducing new bugs or breaking existing functionality.\r\n\r\nEDIT: This should be ready to merge as soon as the tests all pass.",
